# Netlify _redirects — demo subdomain asset safety-net
#
# WHY NO 200 PROXY HERE:
# A 200 proxy (demo.adagi0.com/* → adagi0.com/Demos/:splat) is a cross-domain
# proxy. Netlify changes Host to "adagi0.com" before the SSR function runs, so
# the Astro middleware can no longer detect "isDemoSubdomain" and never patches
# the HTML with absolute asset URLs.
#
# INSTEAD: demo.adagi0.com is a Netlify domain alias. All requests reach the
# SSR function with Host: demo.adagi0.com. The middleware rewrites the path
# (/LinkTree → /Demos/LinkTree) and patches /_astro/ hrefs to absolute URLs
# on adagi0.com so the browser never requests assets from the alias domain.
#
# These rules are just a safety-net in case a browser somehow still requests
# a static asset from the demo subdomain (e.g. old cached page).

https://demo.adagi0.com/_astro/*      https://adagi0.com/_astro/:splat      302!
https://demo.adagi0.com/Cards/*       https://adagi0.com/Cards/:splat       302!
https://demo.adagi0.com/background/*  https://adagi0.com/background/:splat  302!
https://demo.adagi0.com/uploads/*     https://adagi0.com/uploads/:splat     302!
https://demo.adagi0.com/favicon.ico   https://adagi0.com/favicon.ico        302!
https://demo.adagi0.com/favicon.svg   https://adagi0.com/favicon.svg        302!
